PN,30502
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1784132319
OL,3,CWill it rain for the start of the
OL,4,Cschool holidays?
OL,6,FHow long is the sunny weather here for?
OL,8,FCurrently it looks like the sunshine
OL,9,Fwill continue, as high pressure is
OL,10,Fexpected to dominate our weather for a
OL,11,Ffew more days.
OL,13,FIn many areas it's not going to be as
OL,14,Fhot as last week.
OL,16,FTemperatures are widely 25-30C or more
OL,17,Fin parts of England and Wales, with
OL,18,Fmore modest temperatures through
OL,19,FScotland and Northern Ireland.
OL,21,FHow about rain?
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/6
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,306,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30503
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1784132319
OL,3,CWill it rain for the start of the
OL,4,Cschool holidays?
OL,6,FThere's no significant rain forecast
OL,7,Fin the next week to 10 days anywhere
OL,8,Fin the UK.
OL,10,FThere are some thundery downpours
OL,11,Fmoving up through France into the
OL,12,FChannel Islands, and potentially
OL,13,Ftowards southern Cornwall later, but
OL,14,Fmany areas will remain dry.
OL,16,FThere's a low risk of isolated
OL,17,Fthunderstorms developing through the
OL,18,Fsouth and south-west on Thursday.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/6
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,306,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30504
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1784132319
OL,3,CWill it rain for the start of the
OL,4,Cschool holidays?
OL,6,FAlthough thunder is usually associated
OL,7,Fwith heat - we've not got the humid
OL,8,Fair usually associated with such
OL,9,Fconditions.
OL,11,FAt a glance there's a chance of some
OL,12,Fshowery rain developing in places by
OL,13,Fthe end of next week with high
OL,14,Fpressure potentially giving way - much
OL,15,Fof this will be confined to parts of
OL,16,FScotland, Northern Ireland and
OL,17,Fnorthern England.
OL,19,FSo it's staying sunny?
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/6
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
